<HEADLINE> ICRC Team Visits U.S. Prisoners of War Held by Yugoslavia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GENEVA, April 27 (Xinhua) -- A team from the International
Committee of the Red Cross (ICRC) visited the three United States
servicemen held by the Federal Republic of Yugoslavia in Belgrade
Tuesday morning.
</P>
<P>
The three U.S. soldiers were given a medical checkup by a
doctor. The ICRC said that they are in "satisfactory condition".
</P>
<P>
The ICRC delegates held private talks with each prisoner and
registered his personal details. The POWs were also given the
opportunity to write Red Cross messages, which will be forwarded
to their families.
</P>
<P>
The three POWs have been detained since 31 March 1999. ICRC
President Cornelio Sommaruga had an initial brief meeting with
them on Monday during his visit to Yugoslavia. He was given the
official authorization for the ICRC to carry out a full visit
Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The ICRC expressed hope that it could see the three POWs again
during the coming weeks and for as long as they are detained.
</P>
</TEXT>
