<HEADLINE> 6 Israeli Soldiers Injured in S. Lebanon </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIRUT, April 28 (Xinhua) -- Six Israeli soldiers and three
members of the Israel-allied South Lebanon Army (SLA) were wounded
Tuesday afternoon in attacks by Lebanese guerrillas in south
Lebanon.
</P>
<P>
The Iranian-backed Hezbollah, or Party of God, has claimed
responsibility for the attacks, saying one of its group stormed
the Israeli-held post at Sujoud on the edge of the Israeli
occupied border zone in south Lebanon, the Voice of the People
radio reported.
</P>
<P>
Hezbollah fighters wounded all Israeli soldiers at the post
and erected the group's flag on the top of a house.
</P>
<P>
The guerrillas also raided other Israeli posts in the border
zone, the radio added.
</P>
<P>
The Israeli army has confirmed the casualties, which raised to
16 the number of wounded Israeli soldiers since the start of this
year. Another eight were killed over the same period.
</P>
<P>
Israel set up a self-styled security zone in south Lebanon in
1985 with the claimed aim of protecting its north from Lebanese
guerrillas' cross-border attacks.
</P>
<P>
Since then, Lebanon's resistance movement spearheaded by
Hezbollah has been fighting to oust Israeli forces out of the
country.
</P>
<P>
In return, Israeli warplanes raided suspected Hezbollah bases
M14-42NBB189i0427ql01:0801:081403
in the Iqlim Toufaha area just outside the border zone.
</P>
<P>
An Israeli shell landed on the road of Jarjua village only two
kilometers away from Sujoud, wounding a four-year-old boy and his
mother.
</P>
<P>
Israeli artillery forces also bombarded villages and hills in
the country's eastern Bekaa valley. 
</P>
