<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, April 27 (Xinhua) -- President Nelson Mandela
Tuesday left Umtata, about 250 km southwest of Durban, for Russia,
first stop of his last series of official trip abroad, South
African Press Association reported.
</P>
<P>
By Wednesday morning he will be in Moscow, the first leg of an
11-day jet-hopping tour that will also take him to Hungary,
Pakistan and China, Foreign Affairs Department officials were
quoted as saying.
