<HEADLINE> Chinese Official on Falun Gong Practitioners' Gathering </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 27 (Xinhua) -- An official of the Letters and
Calls Departments of the General Offices of the Central Committee
of the Communist Party of China and the State Council was
interviewed by Xinhua today on the April 25 gathering of the Falun
Gong practitioners around the Zhongnanhai compound.
</P>
<P>
The official said that a magazine of a university in Tianjin
recently published a signed article, talking about the Falun Gong.
And some of the practitioners disagreed with what the article said,
so they began on April 19 to make representations to the magazine.
On April 25, some of the practitioners in Beijing, Tianjin and
some other places came to gather around the Zhongnanhai compound,
the central Party and government headquarters, upon hearing some
rumors. Entrusted by authorities concerned, some officials
contacted practitioners in the gathering, listened to them
patiently, and did some persuasion. At the same time, the
aforementioned two departments, along with the Beijing Public
Security Bureau, issued an Announcement, calling on the
practitioners not to believe in rumors, but to observe related
regulations and jointly maintain the capital's public order. The
gathering disappeared after persuasion work on the evening the
same day.
</P>
<P>
The official stressed that governments at all levels have never
prohibited any health fitness activities. He said different views
and opinions are allowable, and can also be reported through
normal channels according to law. But those who have different
views should not gather around the Zhongnanhai, he added.
</P>
<P>
He stressed such kind of gathering would affect the public
order and people's normal life around the headquarters of the CPC
Central Committee and the State Council, and therefore is
completely wrong. He said those who jeopardize social stability
under the pretext of practicing any Gong shall be dealt with
according to law.
</P>
<P>
The official said that China now enjoys a good political,
economic and social situation, which is hard-won. Therefore, it is
necessary to cherish social stability and unity, and
conscientiously maintain them, because it accords with the
people's fundamental interests. 
</P>
</TEXT>
