<HEADLINE> DRC to Hold Multi-Party Debate in Kenya </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DRC Foreign Minister Abdoulaya Yerodia said more than 200
political representatives would be invited to the debate on
constitutional arrangements and democratic elections in DRC.
</P>
<P>
After meeting the Kenyan President Daniel arap Moi, Yerodia
told a press conference that organizing this debate is to stop
the era of arbitrary government and start an era with leaders
elected by the people.
</P>
<P>
Yerodia also noted that the rebels fighting to overthrow
President Laurent Kabila will be invited to the debate, adding
that the debate for Congoleses politicians would go ahead in
Kenya even without the rebels.
</P>
<P>
DRC is ravaged by an eight-month civil war. The rebel Congolese
Rally for Democracy Monday said that it would not attend the
debate and described it as a "circus". 
</P>
</TEXT>
