<HEADLINE> Romania Still Under Threat by Flooding Waters </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUCHAREST, April 27 (Xinhua) -- Recent heavy rainfalls flooded
hundreds of houses and tens of thousands of hectares of farmland,
causing great losses in western, central and southern Romania.
</P>
<P>
According to official sources, the rainfalls hit so far 119
towns and villages, 501 houses and 1,330 households, swamped
33,983 hectares of cropland, swept away numerous bridges and
disrupted road traffic in many places.
</P>
<P>
The central county of Mures has been dealt the heaviest blow,
with three cities and 33 villages awash by rivers spilling their
banks.
</P>
<P>
Head of the Local Public Administration Department Vlad Rosca
decided to allocate funds to help out people suffering from the
floods.
</P>
<P>
The figure of damage caused by inundations in Romania since
early this year was taken to about 50 billion lei, about 3.5
million U.S. dollars.  
</P>
</TEXT>
