<HEADLINE> U.S. Preparing Comprehensive Embargo on Serbia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, April 27 (Xinhua) -- the United States is
preparing a comprehensive embargo on all exports to Serbia,
including oil and other petroleum products but excluding
humanitarian supplies, the State Department said on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
"We are now working through the amendment to the export
administration regulations that are pending -- which would
establish a comprehensive embargo on exports and re-exports to
Serbia of all goods," State Department spokesman James Rubin
told reporters.
</P>
<P>
"This includes exports and re-exports of oil, gasoline and
other petroleum products," he said.
</P>
<P>
Under the amended regulations, any export license from the
Department of Commerce would be required for all exports for
Serbia and the department would deny licenses as a matter of
course, except for humanitarian items, he added.
</P>
<P>
"This is working through the system now. I would expect an
announcement shortly by the Commerce Department," he said.
</P>
<P>
The amendments are to an earlier sanctions package which
included a freeze on the foreign funds of Yugoslav officials and
a ban on export financing and on investment in Serbia. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
