<HEADLINE> ASEAN Police Conference Ends in Hanoi </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, April 28 (Xinhua) - The 19th conference of the
Association of Southeast Asian Nations Police Association
(ASEANAPOL) ended here Wednesday after approving a resolution on
boosting cooperation in fighting transnational criminals among the
member's police forces.
</P>
<P>
During the conference, participants from Brunei, Indonesia,
Laos, Malaysia, Myanmar, the Philippines, Singapore, Thailand and
Vietnam exchanged views on issues including drug smuggling,
criminal archive data and statistics, commercial crimes, banking
crimes, passport fraudulence, transnational swindling and
personnel training.
</P>
<P>
The participants agreed to exchange views and information on
drug smuggling, increase cooperative activities in fighting drug
criminals and promote efficiency of criminal archive data and
statistics systems of ASEANAPOL.
</P>
<P>
At the closing session, a communique was signed by police
commanders of the nine ASEAN countries and a memorandum of
understanding on the exchange of criminal archive data and
statistics was signed by police commanders of seven countries --
Thailand, Singapore, Indonesia, the Philippines, Malaysia, Brunei
and Vietnam.
</P>
<P>
The three-day conference of ASEANAPOL opened on Monday. The
20th conference of ASEANAPOL will be held in Myanmar in 2000.
</P>
</TEXT>
