<DATE_TIME> 1999-04-28 15:48 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Arab League, Russia Discuss Iraqi Issue </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, April 28 (Xinhua) -- Arab League Assistant Secretary
General Ahmad Ben Heli met on Wednesday with Russian Ambassador in
Cairo Vladimir Goudev on issues related to Iraq.
</P>
<P>
Goudev told reporters after the meeting that he and Ben Heli
discussed the situation in Iraq and the debate held in the United
Nations Security Council on the Iraqi issue.
</P>
<P>
He said the Security Council is debating two draft resolutions
on Iraq, adding that one was sponsored by Russia and the other
jointly by Britain and the Netherlands.
</P>
<P>
The Russian blueprint proposes a new monitoring mechanism for
the dismantlement of Iraq's weapons of mass destruction be set up
to replace the U.N. Special Commission and calls for the lifting
of the U.N. economic sanctions on the country, he said.
</P>
<P>
The Western proposal does not mention the lifting of the
economic sanctions and even seeks to impose new restrictions on
the country, in perpetration of keeping the punitive embargo in
place, Goudev said.
</P>
<P>
The Russian diplomat underlined that the Western proposal does
not tally with circumstances in Iraq.
</P>
<P>
The U.N. Security Council imposed the economic embargo on Iraq
in 1990 after its invasion of Kuwait. Destruction of Iraq's banned
weapons is a must for the lifting of the sanctions.
</P>
<P>
Goudev said the Arab League saw Russia's ideas as positive and
constructive, adding that consultations are continuing between the
two sides in a bid to secure approval of the Russian draft
resolution in the Security Council. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
