<HEADLINE> Chinese Women Condemn NATO Bombing of Yugoslavia (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
"Anyone with any sense could not fail to see what the U.S. and
NATO has done. It is obvious that they are trampling on human
rights and creating bloodshed. They are creating a catastrophe for
human society. They are death dealers killing innocent women and
children," it went on.
</P>
<P>
"NATO air strikes have bombed away all our belief in the
frequent and endless western sermons about peace, democracy,
egalitarianism, human rights and disarmament," it said.
</P>
<P>
The U.S. and NATO are creating terrorism and bloodshed
arbitrarily, relying on their economic and military power and
advanced weapons.
</P>
<P>
Their evil deeds have torn down their image, disguised as full
of "humanitarianism and peace" that they had boasted about
incessantly, and exposed their ambitions to throw their weight
about small countries, destroy their opponents, to act as
overlords of the world and create an international order with them
at the core.
</P>
<P>
There is an apt Chinese saying for this state of affairs, "A
just cause enjoys popular support, while an unjust cause finds
little support." History has proved that an invasion has never
succeeded in conquering a sovereignty or nation. All invaders stew
in their own grease at the end and so will NATO.
</P>
<P>
Any invasion is against the will of people all over the world
seeking peace and development, is against the historical tide of
world affairs and will never be supported by the people.
</P>
