<DOCNO> XIE19990428.0073 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-04-28 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Horti-Expo '99 Stimulates Yunnan Tourism in First Quarter </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUNMING, April 28 (Xinhua) -- Thanks to the '99 International
Horticulture Exposition scheduled to open in its provincial
capital of Kunming on May 1, Yunnan Province in southwest China
witnessed a sharp rise in the number of tourists it received in
the first quarter of the year, the provincial tourism
administration reported here today.
</P>
<P>
Statistics show that from January to March, Yunnan received
nearly eight million domestic and foreign tourists and garnered 4.
007 billion yuan (about 500 million US dollars) in total earnings,
a 20.66 percent year-on-year rise.
</P>
<P>
According to a provincial tourism official, the first quarter
used to be a slack tourism season in Yunnan. This year, however,
many tourists, particularly those from overseas regions, have
shown very strong interest in this plateau province in deepest
China after learning that Yunnan will play host to the world
horticultural show.
</P>
<P>
"In the first three months of this year, there was an influx of
700,000 overseas tourists into our province, a 32.6 percent rise
year-on-year," said the official, adding that many of them came
from countries bordering on Yunnan, such as Vietnam, Laos and
Myanmar.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the number of domestic tourists to Yunnan also
exceeded 7.17 million in the period, a 16.75 percent growth over
the same period of 1998, said the official.
</P>
<P>
"This is really a great success for us, as there are many
important festivals, such as the Chinese Lunar New Year, in this
period, during which many people prefer to stay at home for family
reunion instead of traveling around," the official noted.
</P>
<P>
Yunnan expects to attract some 10 million domestic and overseas
tourists during the six-month run of the horticulture exposition.
Local analysts now predict that the actual figure could turn out
to be much higher if the province's tourism sector can maintain
its current growth momentum. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
