<HEADLINE> HK Records Growth in Exchange Fund </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, April 28 (Xinhua) -- Total assets of Hong Kong's
Exchange Fund amounted to 927.1 billion HK dollars (about 118.9
billion U.S. dollars) at the end of March, 5.8 billion HK dollars
(about 743.6 million U.S. dollars) higher than at the end of
February.
</P>
<P>
According to the Exchange Fund Abridged Balance Sheet and
Currency Board Account published by the Hong Kong Monetary
Authority (HKMA) Wednesday, the increase in total assets reflected
an increase of 10.7 billion HK dollars in HK dollar assets, which
was partly offset by a decrease of 5.0 billion HK dollar in
foreign currency assets.
</P>
<P>
In releasing the figures, the HK MA said the increase in HK
dollar assets was mainly due to appreciation in market value of
the Hong Kong equities held by the Exchange Fund, and the decrease
in foreign currency assets can mainly be attributed to reversal in
note issuing activities in March after the Chinese New Year.
</P>
</TEXT>
