<HEADLINE> Earthquake Hits Eastern Romania </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUCHAREST, April 28 (Xinhua) -- An earthquake measuring 5.5 on
the open-ended Richter scale hit eastern Romania on Wednesday, but
so far there has been no official report of casualties.
</P>
<P>
The quake, the strongest in the country since 1990, occurred at
11:47 local time (09:47 GMT) and lasted five seconds, with its
epicenter located in the region of Vrancea, according to the
Romanian Institute of Geophysics.
</P>
<P>
The tremor was felt throughout the country. 
</P>
