<HEADLINE> Senior Chinese, Cuban Officials Discuss Ties (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 28 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Vice-President Hu Jintao
said today that the further growth of relations between China and
Cuba, as well as their communist parties, will help and support
each other, and will serve the healthy development of the cause of
socialism.
</P>
<P>
Hu, also a Standing Committee member of the Political Bureau of
the Chinese Communist Party Central Committee, made the remarks at
a meeting with Jose Ramon Machado, a member of the Political
Bureau of the Cuban Communist Party Central Committee and vice-
president of the Council of State.
</P>
<P>
Hu extended his congratulations on the 40 anniversary of the
victory of the Cuban revolution, and said that the Cuban people
have scored gratifying achievements in the socialist revolution
and building up the country under the leadership of the Cuban
Communist Party headed by Fidel Castro Ruz. They have also
overcome various kinds of difficulties facing them on the way and
held firm against the changing international situation.
</P>
<P>
The Cuban party and government have made enormous efforts and
remarkable progress in stabilizing the society, restoring economic
growth, improving people's standards of living and trying to gain
international support in recent years, he said, adding that China
admires and is pleased with this.
</P>
<P>
Hu recalled his 1997 visit to Cuba, saying that the two parties
and governments enjoy long standing friendship and cooperation. He
added that relations between the two parties and governments have
seen further growth through the efforts made by leaders of the two
countries in recent years.
</P>
</TEXT>
