<HEADLINE> Israeli Military Closes Jenin Area "A" </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM, April 28 (Xinhua) -- The Israeli military on
Wednesday closed the Area "A" of Jenin in the West Bank following
a shotting incident in which an Israeli Defense Force (IDF) soldier
was wounded, according to a senior Palestinian Security officer.
</P>
<P>
The Israeli military announced the closure of Area "A" and
turned it into a military zone shortly after the shotting incident
Wednesday noon, the officer said.
</P>
<P>
Palestinian security forces opened fire at and wounded the IDF
solider who attempted to enter the area near Saylat Al-Harithiya
village north of Jenin, the officer said.
</P>
<P>
The Palestinian forces asked the soldier to stop, but he went
on in defiance of the warning, the officer added.
</P>
<P>
Earlier, the Israeli army said the IDF soldier was shot and
wounded in a village north of Jenin when an unknown gunman opened
fire at him.
</P>
<P>
The gunman fled away in a civilian car and the IDF and police
are investing the case, the army said.
</P>
<P>
This was the third shooting incident that occurred in the West
Bank since the beginning of the year.
</P>
<P>
On January 4, a Palestinian gunman opened fire at a Jewish
settler's van and wounded three women settlers in Hebron.
</P>
<P>
Two days later, the IDF troops in the city shot dead a
Palestinian youth named Badar Kawasshmeh.
</P>
<P>
In the West Bank, Area "A" is under total Palestinian control,
while in Area "B" the security affairs are in the hands of the
Israeli military and civil affairs under the Palestinian
administration. Area "C" is totally under Israeli control.
</P>
<P>
Under the Wye peace accord signed by Israel and the
Palestinian National Authority last october, Israel had pullout
its troops from most of the Jenin area by the end of last
year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
