<HEADLINE> Major Chinese Trade Fair Attracts More Overseas Visitors </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, April 28 (Xinhua) -- New records have been set by
the 85th Guangzhou Export Commodity Trade Fair which has seen tens
of thousands of business people from outside China flocking to the
event.
</P>
<P>
By Tuesday, more than 74,900 people from 171 countries and
regions had visited China's oldest and largest export trade fair,
almost 17 percent more than the previous fair.
</P>
<P>
At the same time, the fair had a trade volume of nine billion
US dollars, ten percent higher than last year's.
</P>
<P>
Ren Guangbin, a fair official, said that it has attracted more
and more new business people from around the world in recent years.
</P>
<P>
Last year, however, owing to the financial crisis, the number
of Asian business people attending the fair was reduced
significantly, the official said.
</P>
<P>
But this current fair has so far attracted 52,000 business
people from Asian countries and regions, 16.3 percent up on last
year.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the number of business people from European and
African countries such as Russia, Argentina, Chile and South
Africa is also increasing. 
</P>
