<HEADLINE> Shanghai Attracts Birds </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, April 28 (Xinhua) -- China's largest industrial and
commercial city of Shanghai has attracted large numbers of birds
in recent years.
</P>
<P>
A recent survey shows the city is now home to 429 species of
bird, of which, about 200 are under the protection of
international conventions.
</P>
<P>
Experts attribute this to an improving environment resulting
from the increasing awareness of the importance of environmental
protection among local residents.
</P>
<P>
Rapid economic development and urban expansion had posed a
threat to the habitat of birds in the city, and local
ornithologists had been worried about it.
</P>
<P>
The city launched an annual "Love Birds Week" 18 years ago, and
has since spread knowledge about birds among millions of local
residents.
</P>
<P>
Last year, the municipal government set up a nature reserve on
Chongming Island to protect the habitat of rare birds.
</P>
<P>
The reserve, which is on a major migratory route for many birds,
has become a wintering place for some 100 bird species, including
cranes and storks.  
</P>
</TEXT>
