<HEADLINE> Estrada Vows to Pursue Budget Reforms in Philippines </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, April 28 (Xinhua) -- Philippine President Joseph
Estrada Wednesday reaffirmed his commitment to instituting reforms
in the government's expenditure program to ensure fiscal
discipline and efficiency.
</P>
<P>
He said these reforms include a shift from the present
cost-based method of managing public funds to the more efficient
performance-based procedure.
</P>
<P>
The reforms will also help his administration's campaign
against graft and corruption by promoting transparency and
integrity, Estrada said at the 63rd anniversary celebration of the
Department of Budget and Management.
</P>
<P>
"Let's always remember that most of the funds spent by the
government come from the efforts of our countrymen, like small
farmers, fishermen, laborers and small entrepreneurs and ordinary
employees," he said.
</P>
<P>
Estrada said he was pleased with the series of reforms
implemented by the department, among which is the formation of the
Budget Dialogue Group.
</P>
<P>
The group ensures the high-level representation and
participation of the cabinet, legislature, the business community,
experts and the people in the formulation of the national budget,
he said.
</P>
<P>
The group will also be involved in drafting rules and
procedures on how to come up with a medium-term budget framework
that aims to identify priority government programs, he added.
</P>
</TEXT>
