<HEADLINE> Retired Model Workers Attend Reception in Beijing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 28 (Xinhua) -- One hundred old people who were
well-known as "model workers" throughout China decades ago today
were in the spotlight again, as they attended a reception in
Beijing's Diaoyutai State Guesthouse.
</P>
<P>
The event just ahead of International Labor Day on May 1 aimed
to honor the great achievements that the retired workers had made
to the country, according to the China National Committee on
Ageing (CNAC), the country's largest non-governmental organization
of old people.
</P>
<P>
State Councilor Ismail Amat said at the reception that the once
elite workers had played an active role in promoting social
progress and now they deserved the care and respect of the whole
society especially because of their seniority.
</P>
<P>
He recalled that President Jiang Zemin recently wrote words of
encouragement to demonstrate support for those working on behalf
of senior citizens.
</P>
<P>
The CNAC had invited the old people to Beijing from different
parts of the country, organizing sightseeing programs for them, as
well as letting them take part in seminars on population ageing
issues.
</P>
<P>
"Organizing such events was part of the CNAC's efforts to
arouse the public awareness of the value of old persons," said an
official with the association.
</P>
<P>
He admitted that prejudice, even discrimination, still exist in
the country due to ignorance about old people's contributions, as
well as an underestimation of their value. And the work in this
field has become more and more urgent since China's ageing
population is expanding rapidly.
</P>
<P>
The number of people aged 60 and older will reach 130 million
in China next year, accounting for one tenth of the total
population.  
</P>
