<HEADLINE> State Council Approves Reforms of Scientific Awards </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 28 (Xinhua) -- Reforms of the scientific award
system and regulations governing other state scientific and
technological awards were approved today at an executive meeting
of the State Council, which was presided over by Premier Zhu
Rongji.
</P>
<P>
Scientific awards are an important part of the state policy on
science and technology, and the reforms are beneficial for
establishing and improving the state's scientific innovation
program through following the principle of "revitalizing the
country through science and education", the meeting was told.
</P>
<P>
The major measures of the reforms include establishing a high
state prize for scientific achievements, improving the state
science and technology award system, strengthening the management
and inspection of government departments for local and social
scientific awards
</P>
<P>
Regulations on the state science and technology award system
will be published by the State Council after revision as will
details of the reforms. 
