<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 28 (Xinhua) -- Premier Zhu Rongji said here
today that China cherishes Sino-Kenyan traditional ties, and would
like to push forward the bilateral relations on the basis of the
Five Principles of Peaceful Co-Existence.
</P>
<P>
He told visiting Kenyan Foreign Minister Bonaya Godana during
their meeting that the understanding and trust between the
governments and peoples of the two countries have been deepened
since the two countries established diplomatic relations 35 years
ago.
</P>
<P>
"The bilateral cooperation in a wide range of areas has scored
achievements, and the two countries always support each other in
international affairs," Zhu said.
</P>
<P>
He noted that the bilateral ties, promoted by the top leaders
of the two countries, have entered a new stage of development
which is marked by sincerity, friendship and comprehensive
cooperation.
</P>
<P>
He expressed his belief that the current visit of Godana will
serve to consolidate bilateral relations.
</P>
