<HEADLINE> Russia, Pakistan to Build Strong Links: Seleznev </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, April 28 (Xinhua) -- The Russian parliamentary
leader said here Wednesday that both Russia and Pakistan are
keenly interested in building strong bridges between the two
nations in all directions.
</P>
<P>
Guennadey N. Seleznev, Chairman of the Russian State Duma, was
talking told newsmen at the Islamabad airport that he was
confident both Russia and Pakistan want to build
inter-governmental and inter-parliamentary ties.
</P>
<P>
Referring to the recent visit to Russia by Prime Minister Nawaz
Sharif, Seleznev, who arrived for a three-day visit to Pakistan,
said the two sides had "very business-like, substantive and
fruitful dialogue."
</P>
<P>
There is a need to increase cooperation between Pakistan and
Russia in all fields, especially in trade, economy, scientific and
cultural programs and space exploration for the benefit of the two
countries and the two peoples, he said.
</P>
<P>
He also said the members of the Russian Parliament are
interested in maintaining and developing stronger ties with
Pakistan.
</P>
<P>
Seleznev, accompanied by a 49-member entourage including eight
members of the State Duma, is here at the invitation of his
Pakistani counterpart Illahi Bukhsh Soomro, who visited Moscow in
March last year.
</P>
<P>
During his stay here, Seleznev is scheduled to meet President
Rafiq Tarar, Prime Minister Sharif and other high-ranking
government officials, as well as National Assembly Speaker Soomro
and Senate Chairman Wasim Sajjad.
</P>
<P>
The Russian parliamentary delegation will stay in the capital
city Islamabad for two days, and will also visit Lahore, the
provincial capital of Punjab. 
