<HEADLINE> Shandong Develops Environment Friendly Motorcycles </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JINAN, April 28 (Xinhua) -- Environment friendly motorcycles
which use a new technology to reduce exhaust emissions have been
developed by the Qingqi Group, China's motorcycle giant based in
Jinan, capital of east Shandong Province.
</P>
<P>
The volume of both carbon monoxide and hydrocarbon emitted by
the "green" motorcycles has been reduced by more than 70 percent
compared with the group's older machines.
</P>
<P>
Indeed, the emission level is much lower than the official
country limit for motorcycles and is actually of international
standard, according to the provincial environment inspection
center.
</P>
<P>
Such "green" products indicate that China is now able to
control pollution caused by motorcycle exhausts.
</P>
<P>
With a total of 14 billion yuan worth of capital, The Qingqi
Group has three listed companies. It has over 80 sale outlets
scattered across the country.
</P>
<P>
The group turned out 1.7 million motorcycles in 1998 and ranked
first in the country not only for sales but also profits. 
</P>
</TEXT>
