<HEADLINE> Share Prices Plunge on Singapore Stock Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, April 28 (Xinhua) -- Share prices plunged on
Singapore Stock Market Wednesday reversing early gains buoyed by
the overnight record rise at Wall Street.
</P>
<P>
The benchmark Straits Times Index lost 39.23 point to end at
1,837.16 points, falling from the intraday high of 1901.06, the
highest level in the past 18-months.
</P>
<P>
The total volume extended to 623.87 million units worth 807.05
million Singapore dollars (475.63 million U.S. dollars). Losers
outstripped gainers by 316 to 54 with 68 counters unchanged.
</P>
<P>
Lian Beng topped the most actives chart with a hefty 35.61
million shares traded. ST Engg was the second most heavily traded
stock with a turnover of 21.14 million units. LKN was the next
which saw 18.32 million counters changing hands.
</P>
<P>
Asean 100 headed the ascent of the day soaring by 180 cents to
close at 4.00 Singapore dollars. C&AMP;C rose 60 cents to 10.09
Singapore dollars on news that sales of passenger cars in Malaysia
last month almost trebled year-on-year. DBS F gained 30 cents to
end at 18.10 Singapore dollars.
</P>
<P>
On the downside, Creative 50 incurred the sharpest fall of 200
cents and closed at 21.40 Singapore dollars. SPH 100 sank 160
cents to finish at 23.50 Singapore dollars. SPH lost 150 cents to
end at 23.60 Singapore dollars.
</P>
<P>
Today's reversal was the market's most severe since the
beginning of the month when it embarked on a rally that has pushed
the STI up some 20 percent.
</P>
<P>
Shares lost the running-up momentum after breaching the 1,900
mark in early trading and the index plunged sharply failing to
overcome the strong resistance.
</P>
<P>
Some dealers complained the market has gone way too much above
fundamentals. 
</P>
</TEXT>
