<HEADLINE> State Council Approves Draft Regulation for Rewarding Research Findings </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 28 (Xinhua) -- The 16th meeting of the Executive
Committee of the State Council, which was presided over by Premier
Zhu Rongji, today approved in principle a draft regulation for
rewarding research findings and a plan to reform the system for
rewarding such findings.
</P>
<P>
As an important part of the state's science and technology
policy, the reward system will help to implement the strategy of
invigorating the nation through science and education, said
participants at the meeting.
</P>
<P>
At the meeting it was suggested that nationwide rewards be
introduced for the top achievers and to improve rewards in other
fields.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, participants agreed that the central authorities
should effectively manage and guide various types of rewards for
research findings, which are granted by various departments,
localities and non-governmental organizations.
</P>
<P>
The Regulation on Rewarding Scientific and Technological
Findings will be promulgated by the State Council following
revisions. The Plan to reform the System for Rewarding Scientific
and Technological Research Findings will be distributed by the
State Council.
</P>
<P>
Participants also discussed the notice of the General Office of
the State Council on questions concerning the relocation of
residents from the reservoir area of the Three Gorges project on
the Yangtze River. 
</P>
