<HEADLINE> China to Host Agriculture, Food Technology Exhibition </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 28 (Xinhua) -- China will hold an international
agriculture and food technology exhibition in Beijing between
April 11-14 next year.
</P>
<P>
The exhibition, titled Agro Food-Tech China, will be jointly
sponsored by the China Council for the Promotion of International
Trade's Specialized Sub-council of Agriculture (CCPIT-SSA) and
Exposium, France's largest exhibition group.
</P>
<P>
The exhibition is expected to boost China's agricultural
modernization by combining the agricultural and food processing
industries, according to an official with the CCPIT-SSA.
</P>
<P>
She also noted that the exhibition will provide an opportunity
for overseas and domestic companies to cooperate with each other.
</P>
<P>
The first such exhibition, also sponsored by the CCPIT-SSA and
Exposium, was held on April 20-23 this year, with more than 350
firms from 18 countries and regions bringing their products to
Beijing.  
</P>
</TEXT>
