<DATE_TIME> 1999-04-28 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Macao to Implement Compulsory Education </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, April 28 (Xinhua) -- Macao will carry out compulsory
schooling among primary and secondary school students on the basis
of current ten-year free education, local educational sources said.
</P>
<P>
The Education and Youth Department of the Macao government is
working on a decree about compulsory schooling, which is expected
to be put into force in a couple of months, according to Luis
Amado de Viseu, the director of the department.
</P>
<P>
The decree would require that all children and young people of
school age attend school. As the first step, the decree would be
implemented among primary school pupils.
</P>
<P>
The director explained that Macao's educational conditions are
good enough to carry out compulsory schooling. About 80 percent of
local schools have joined the government's free education program,
and a system to assist kids from poor families has been set up.
</P>
<P>
In addition, there have been adequate school facilities in
Macao to accommodate children and young people of school age
following concerted efforts by the government and some social
organizations over the past years. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
