<HEADLINE> Traffic Accidents Increase in South Korea </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SEOUL, April 28 (Xinhua) -- The number of traffic accidents
rose in South Korea in the first quarter of this year while the
number of casualties fell, the National Police Agency said
Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The traffic accidents nationwide numbered at 53,772 in the
first three months, up 9.2 percent from the same period last year.
The number of deaths dropped 6.8 percent to 1,960 after increased
use of automated radar on highways.
</P>
<P>
Police said most of the deaths -- 1,294 cases -- resulted from
reckless driving. 
</P>
</TEXT>
