<HEADLINE> China Issues Registered Treasury Bonds </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 28 (Xinhua) -- China is to issue 16 billion yuan
(nearly two billion US dollars) worth of registered treasury bonds
on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The Ministry of Finance announced today that the ten-year bonds
will have an interest rate of 4.72 percent. The interest will be
paid on an annual basis.
</P>
<P>
This is the second batch of registered treasury bonds that
China has issued this year.
</P>
<P>
Thirty six Chinese banks and insurance companies signed the
agreement with the Ministry of Finance to underwrite the bonds
here today.
</P>
<P>
Sources from the ministry said that only the Chinese legal
person entities that China's central bank approved to enter the
inter-bank bond market are allowed to underwrite the bonds.
</P>
</TEXT>
