<DATE_TIME> 1999-04-28 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Breeds Herb With Biggest Leaf in World </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUNMING, April 28 (Xinhua) -- Chinese botanists have succeeded
in breeding a herb whose leaf can cover up three horses standing
in a row with their riders.
</P>
<P>
The young plant, known as "Gunnera Manicata" native to Chile,
is now growing in the Alpine Plant Hall of the Grand Greenhouse at
the China '99 Kunming International Horticultural Exposition,
which is scheduled to open on May 1 in the capital of Southwest
China's Yunnan province.
</P>
<P>
"This indicated that China has the conditions of growing such
plant in wider areas," said Sun Weibang, associate research fellow
with the Kunming Institute of Botany under the Chinese Academy of
Sciences.
</P>
<P>
Sun studied the plant when he was studying in Britain some
years ago and mastered the key techniques for breeding the herb.
Upon his departure for China, Nown, director of the Royal
Botanical Garden Edinburgh gave him a plant of the herb as a gift.
</P>
<P>
Sun took good care of the plant ever since, keeping it under
low temperature, humid conditions and watering it. The plant
regained vitality by the end of 1994, and has grown over one meter
high at present.
</P>
<P>
Sun collected seeds of the herb, bred them and transplanted one
of them in the Grand Greenhouse of the Kunming Exposition '99.
</P>
<P>
"Although it is only 20 centimeters in height at present, the
exotic plant is sure to grow into one that will catch the
attention of visitors." Sun said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
