<HEADLINE> China's Real Estate in Favorable Climate </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The report jointly issued by the National Bureau of Statistics
and the China Business Climate Monitoring Center attributes the
rise to the government's pro-active financial policies and stable
monetary measures to spur economic development, which boost the
real estate industry.
</P>
<P>
In 1998, the country launched three building programs for low-
price houses, which sent the whole real estate sector soaring.
</P>
<P>
The report noted that the first quarter of this year witnessed
an increase in developed land and investments in the industry
along with a drop in the number of unsold buildings.
</P>
<P>
In the January-March period, the country developed 7.4 million
sq.m. of land, up 93 percent over the same period last year.
</P>
<P>
The investments in real estate development totaled 41.3 billion
yuan, up 19.4 percent on a year on year basis.
</P>
<P>
But the indices for newly constructed areas, sources of funding
for this year, and the housing prices edged down in March,
according to the report. 
</P>
</TEXT>
