<HEADLINE> America Online Reports High Earnings for 3rd Quarter </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LOS ANGELES, April 28 (Xinhua) -- America Online (AOL) Inc.,
the world's leading Internet service provider, announced Tuesday
that its third quarter net income tripled as revenue soared 66
percent.
</P>
<P>
A report from the company said earnings for the three months
ended March 31 increased to 117 million U.S. dollars, up from 39
million dollars a year ago.
</P>
<P>
Revenue rose to nearly 1.3 billion dollars -- the first one-
billion-dollar quarter in the company's 14-year history.
Advertising and electronic commerce revenues, a key benchmark of
Internet business performance, rose 119 percent to 210 million
dollars, and subscription revenues were up 50 percent to 869
million dollars, the company said.
</P>
<P>
"This was a pivotal quarter for America Online," AOL Chairman
and CEO Steve Case said Tuesday. "Through key acquisitions and
partnerships, we substantially broadened and deepened our
capabilities, and advanced our leadership in interactive services.
"
</P>
<P>
He was referring to the AOL's acquisition of Netscape for
nearly 10 billion dollars on March 17.
</P>
<P>
Including effects of its merger with Netscape and other one-
time events, the AOL reported consolidated net income of 420
billion dollars versus a net loss of 78 million dollars during the
same period last year.
</P>
<P>
The AOL has nearly 17 million members, plus another two million
subscribers through its Compuserve subsidiary. During the third
quarter, a record number of 1.8 million new customers became its
members. 
</P>
</TEXT>
