<HEADLINE> Premature Baby Making Good Progress </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENYANG, April 28 (Xinhua) -- A tiny premature baby weighing
only 750 grams has survived his first 30 days in local maternity
hospital of Shenyang, capital of northeast China's Liaoning
Province.
</P>
<P>
The infant boy, who is still in an incubator, is the smallest
and lightest baby ever born in northeast China.
</P>
<P>
According to hospital sources, Zhang Fengxia, a woman from
Liaoning's countryside, gave birth to the baby on March 29 after
only 29 weeks of pregnancy. Before this premature delivery Zhang
had suffered five abortions.
</P>
<P>
At birth, the baby was breathless and only had 60 to 80
heartbeats per second, much lower than the 120 per second for
normal babies. He was immediately transferred to an incubator to
be kept alive through artificial means.
</P>
<P>
On day 24 he was able for the first time to take milk unaided.
</P>
<P>
The boy's weight has now increased to 1,400 grams and hospital
sources say once it reaches 1,800 grams it will be safe for him to
be discharged.
</P>
<P>
The survival rate of premature babies weighing less than 2,500
grams in China is less than 60 percent. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19990428.0228 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-04-28 </DATE_TIME>
