<HEADLINE> 12 Tamil Rebels Killed in Fresh Fighting in S.Lanka </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, April 28 (Xinhua) -- Sri Lankan government troops
killed 12 Tamil rebels in separate clashes on Monday and Tuesday
in the north of the country, a Defense Ministry spokesman said
Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Government troops on Monday killed seven rebels, including two
women cadres in Thadduvankoddy in Jaffna, the spokesman said in a
press release.
</P>
<P>
The spokesman said troops sniped and killed one rebel in
Kamarikalakulam in Jaffna on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Also on Tuesday, troops killed three rebels in a bunker
northwest of Mankulam in northern Wanni and one rebel north of
Mankulam in Wanni.
</P>
<P>
The Tamil rebels have been fighting a separatist war against
the Sri Lankan government since 1983 for an independent Tamil
homeland in the north and east of the country. 
