<HEADLINE> EDS-Update with Afternoon Talks China, EU Resume WTO Group Talks for Third Day </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 28 (Xinhua)-- China and the European Union (EU)
resumed group talks on China's entry into the World Trade
Organization (WTO) for the third day, focusing on the tariffs on
goods trade, and service trade.
</P>
<P>
Long Yongtu, chief trade negotiator of the Ministry of Foreign
Trade and Economic Cooperation (MOFTEC), met with Gerard Depayre,
deputy director-general of Directorate General 1 of EC, here for
about 30 minutes in the afternoon. The topics of their discussion
have not been revealed.
</P>
<P>
Seven members of the EU delegation participated in Wednesday's
group talks, which were conducted in two groups.
</P>
<P>
The current round of talks between China and the EU started
here Monday morning, before negotiations between China and the U.S.
on the remaining issues concerning China's accession to the WTO
concluded. The China-EU talks are expected to last for one week.
</P>
<P>
Long told Xinhua on Monday that China is prepared to make the "
utmost efforts" to push forward negotiations with the EU and will
strive to achieve important progress as soon as possible.
</P>
<P>
According to the top Chinese negotiator, the European side has
expressed "firm support" for China's entry into WTO within the
year 1999. 
</P>
