<HEADLINE>   Heat Center Mourning out Indefinitely with Eye Injury </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, April 27 (Xinhua) -- All-Star center of the Miami
Heat Alonzo Mourning is out indefinitely after suffering an eye
injury in Monday's 90-65 victory in Cleveland.
</P>
<P>
The injury comes at a bad time for the Heat, who are battling
for the top seed in the Eastern Conference. At 30-14, they lead
Indiana by 1 1/2 games, Orlando by two and Atlanta by 2 1/2, with
six remaining.
</P>
<P>
Mourning is no stranger to injury, having missed an average of
nearly 14 games over his first six seasons. Last year, he wore a
protective mask that covered most of his face after breaking his
left cheekbone.
</P>
<P>
The 6-10, four-time All-Star leads the league in blocked shots
at 4.0 per game, is 12th in scoring (20.3), seventh in rebounds (
11.1 and ninth in field-goal percentage (.511).
</P>
<P>
A physical, intimidating force, Mourning also is the leader of
the NBA's best defense. The Heat have allowed a league-low 82.8
points per game.
</P>
<P>
Mourning is in his fourth season with Miami. He has averaged
more than 20 points and 10 rebounds during his career, which began
with Charlotte in 1992. 
</P>
</TEXT>
