<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese Securities Companies Granted More Accesses to Money Raising </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 28 (Xinhua) -- Chinese securities companies will
be given access to new money raising channels including inter-bank
lending and borrowing and bond repurchasing markets, according to
the China Securities industry's watchdog.
</P>
<P>
Zhou Zhengqing, chairman of the China Securities Regulatory
Commission (CSRC), was quoted by Wednesday's People's Daily as
saying that more policies governing financing sources of
securities companies are under way.
</P>
<P>
Zhou said in a speech early in March that securities companies
are entitled to the same money raising rights as other financial
institutions.
</P>
<P>
According to China's first Securities Law promulgated last
December, securities firms will be classified into two groups.
Companies with registered capital above 500 million yuan may have
access to business lines ranging from underwriting of new stocks
to brokerage, while companies with registered capital between 50-
500 million yuan will be confined to brokerage.
</P>
<P>
"The new money raising channels will help prevent
irregularities amongst securities companies by giving them more
accesses to the capital market," Zhou said.
</P>
<P>
He also mentioned new regulations for investment funds, under
which they will be issued by existing fund management companies.
</P>
<P>
The regulations are aimed at reducing the outlay of those
companies and expanding the proportion of institutional investors
in the stock market, he said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
