<HEADLINE> Zhejiang Province Launches Green Hotels Program </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANGZHOU, April 28 (Xinhua) -- East China's Zhejiang Province,
renowned as a tourist haven, today launched a campaign to improve
the image of local hotels by increasing environment friendly
awareness among them.
</P>
<P>
The green hotel campaign is one of a series of major activities
scheduled for the province's 1999 ecological tourism year program.
It is being sponsored by the Provincial Tourism bureau, the
Provincial Planning and Economic Commission, and the Provincial
Environmental Protection Bureau.
</P>
<P>
Local hotels are being urged to provide services which favor
the use of local resources and environmental protection as well as
being good for people's health.
</P>
<P>
The province now has 387 hotels designed for overseas visitors
with a total of 50,000 rooms, 193 of which are star-rated with a
total of 30,000 rooms and have a province wide information and
service network.
</P>
<P>
During recent years, the province has spared no efforts to
standardize the local hotel business by introducing scientific
management methods, in an effort to give a big push to the
development of the local tourism industry. 
</P>
</TEXT>
