<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Well-Known Chinese Musician Dies </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, April 28 (Xinhua) -- He Luting, a famous Chinese
composer and music teacher, died here on Tuesday at the age of 96.
</P>
<P>
A native of Shaoyang, central China's Hunan Province, He Luting
served as deputy president of China's Central Conservatory of
Music, president and honorary president of the Shanghai
Conservatory of Music, vice-chairman of the All-China Federation
of Literary and Art Circles, vice-chairman and honorary chairman
of Chinese Musicians' Association, and deputy president of the
Sino-Hungarian Friendship Association.
</P>
<P>
In China He was well known as "the people's musician" and wrote
more than 260 songs, such as Songs of the Guerrilla, the East is
Red, In the Spring, and Shepherd Flute.
</P>
<P>
Since the People's Republic of China was founded in 1949, the
musician had devoted the main part of his effort to teaching music
and was responsible for nurturing a large number of musical
professionals.
</P>
<P>
Last year, the musician was given Shanghai Municipality's top
honor for literature and art, the prestigious "Award of
Outstanding Contributions".  
</P>
</TEXT>
