<HEADLINE> Sri Lanka Trains Volunteers to Counsel War Widows </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, April 28 (Xinhua) -- Sri Lanka has trained a batch of
volunteers to counsel war widows who are facing immense
psychological problems, officials said Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
It was the first training program launched to provide succor to
war widows by the Ex-Servicemen's Association in conjunction with
the Association of Retired Flag Rank Officers and the Psychiatric
Association.
</P>
<P>
Thirty counselors, who have qualified after a training seminar,
will fan out throughout the country to counsel over 300 army
widows who are in need of this service, they said.
</P>
<P>
Ex-Servicemen's Association hoped to conduct three to four
"train the counselors" programs in the future. 
</P>
</TEXT>
