<HEADLINE> Poland Imposes Oil Embargo on Yugoslavia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WARSAW, April 27 (Xinhua) -- The Polish government on Tuesday
announced to stop exporting oil and oil products to Yugoslavia in
line with the stance of NATO and European Union on the Kosovo
crisis.
</P>
<P>
The decision, effective upon announcement, was made at a
routine governmental meeting.
</P>
<P>
The Warsaw Life Daily quoted Minister of National Defense
Janusz Onyszkiewicz as saying that Poland, a NATO member since
last month, would send ships to participate in sea blockade of
Yugoslavia.
</P>
<P>
A spokesman for the Polish Navy headquarters said that 157
ships and supporting vessels and 85 warplanes and helicopters are
ready to act any time. 
</P>
</TEXT>
