<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Cancer Deaths Rise in Mexico </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MEXICO CITY, April 27 (Xinhua) -- The Mexican Health
Authorities on Tuesday gave an alert of the rise of deaths from
cancer.
</P>
<P>
Without giving specific figures, Dolores Gallardo, chief of the
Division of Education for Health of the National Institute of
Cancerology, said that now deaths from cancer have ranked second
among all the causes in the country, compared to the fifteenth
place 30 years ago.
</P>
<P>
She attributed this to the bad life-styles, such as the lack of
exercise, smoking as well as eating too much high-fat food and
little fruits and vegetables.
</P>
<P>
The largest number of cases are connected with tumors,
bronchial tubes, oral cavities, larynx, stomach, intestine and
colon.
</P>
<P>
Women have a higher incidence than men, with womb and breast
cancers accounting for 25 and 13 percent respectively. 
</P>
</TEXT>
