<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 35 Killed as Train Rams Into Bus in India </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, April 28 (Xinhua) -- At least 35 people were killed
and 40 others seriously injured when a bus carrying a marriage
party collided with an express train at an unmanned crossing in
Uttar Pradesh of northern India Tuesday night, The Statesman said
here Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
About 27 people died on the spot while eight succumbed to
injuries in hospital. The level crossing did not have gates to
direct road traffic. 
</P>
