<BODY>
<HEADLINE> NATO New Concept Aims to Dominate Europe, World Affairs: Russia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, April 27 (Xinhua) -- A statement issued Tuesday by the
Russian Foreign Ministry said that NATO's new concept of strategy,
adopted recently at its Washington summit, aimed to enable the
alliance to dominate in affairs of Europe and the world.
</P>
<P>
The statement noted that this concept is not only no good to
Europe's security but also no help for NATO members to carry out
their international commitments within the authorization of the
United Nations and Organization for Security and Cooperation in
Europe (OSCE).
</P>
<P>
It held that security in Europe should cover all countries in
the continent and all of them should be equally treated.
</P>
<P>
NATO has officially renounced the bloc's original defense
strategy by unveiling the new concept, which allows the bloc to
take any actions, including military ones, outside the territories
of its member countries when necessary, the statement said, adding
this is against the pronouncement it made in the concept that the
UN Security Council should play a principal role in maintaining
peace and stability in the world.
</P>
<P>
Regarding the issue of preventing mass destructive weapons
mentioned in the alliance's formal document, it stressed the issue
can only be settled under international norms and atmosphere of
trust among countries concerned.
</P>
<P>
Russia, which reaffirmed its long-term opposition to NATO's
eastward expansion, expressed worries over NATO's announcement
that the expansion will not be restricted by geographic boundaries,
it added.
</P>
<P>
The statement loudly called on NATO to stop bombing Yugoslavia,
which has entered day 34, and bring the Kosovo crisis back to the
track of political settlement.
</P>
<P>
In conclusion, it urged Washington, which has repeatedly asked
for partnership with Moscow recently, to take concrete actions
instead of words only. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
