<DATE_TIME> 1999-04-28 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Myanmar Seizes 262 Kilos of Drugs in March </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YANGON, April 28 (Xinhua) -- Myanmar seized a total of 262
kilograms (kg) of narcotic drugs, including 9.23 kg heroin and
97.62 kg opium, in March, official newspaper The New Light of
Myanmar reported Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Army units, police and the customs also confiscated 17.59 kg
marijuana, 56.16 liters of phensedyl and 147,907 tablets of
stimulant drugs.
</P>
<P>
During the month, the authorities punished 583 persons,
including 483 men and 100 women, involved in 429 drug-related
cases, the report said.
</P>
<P>
In the 1998-99 opium cultivation season, the Myanmar
authorities destroyed a total of 3,839 hectares of poppy fields
scattered in Shan, Kayah and Kachin states and Mandalay division
in the country.
</P>
<P>
According to official statistics, 10,794 kg narcotic drugs,
including 403.8 kg heroin and 5,393.6 kg opium as well as 16.02
million stimulant drug tablets, were seized in the country last
year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
