<DOCNO> XIE19990428.0275 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-04-28 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Dali: Phantom of Harmony between Man and Nature (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUNMING, April 28 (Xinhua) -- It is charismatic and charming.
The natural scenes, the dexterous and industrious people and the
stories behind them have made this ancient little town of Dali the
phantom of harmony between man and nature.
</P>
<P>
As early as in the 13th century, Italian traveller Marco Polo
recorded a story about how boas, mysterious horses and local
residents lived harmoniously together.
</P>
<P>
The kind people and the picturesque landscape also amazed the
contemporary Chinese action novelist Louis Cha Leung-yung, who
fabricated a "Kingdom of Dali" that gives a vivid description of
the wise kings, amiable people and the fascinating landscape. Mr.
Louis Cha Leung-yung, whose influence in the Chinese-speaking
world is comparable to that of Stephen King in the English-
speaking world, has never been to Dali and it remains a mystery as
to why he was so charmed by this little border town. Dali city
honored him as an "honorary citizen".
</P>
<P>
 Dali is a famous ancient town, situated in the northwestern
part of Yunnan Province. It served as the capital of the State of
Nan Zhao and the State of Dali from the 8th through the 13th
centuries. It was later conquered by Kublai Khan, the fifth
emperor of the Yuan Dynasty, and was incorporated into the map of
the Yuan Dynasty. Now the little town is still shrouded with the
mysteries of the ancient states and beauty of the landscape. It
fully deserves to have been chosen as a sub-site of the China '99
Kunming International Horticultural Exposition that has "man and
nature, marching towards the 21st century" as its theme.
</P>
<P>
Streets of the town are paved with flagstones and lined with
wooden dwelling houses just as it was more than one thousand years
ago. Lining the winding streets are also stores and workshops
featuring such beautiful arts and crafts as needlework, hand-made
shoes, knitwear, embroideries and wooden products
</P>
<P>
But the most renowned should be Mount Cangshan and the Erhai
Lake. The thick and exuberant forests and ever-changing scenes of
the lake as rosy clouds rise from the water surface are enough to
make visitors carried away. It is said that fish weighing as much
as hundreds of kilograms was once caught in the lake.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19990428.0276 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-04-28 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Dali: Phantom of Harmony between Man and Nature (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The town is mainly inhabited by people of the Bai nationality.
In their traditional costumes and with their long hair coiled into
complicated finesse topknot modeling on flamboyant flowers, young
girls are good hands in cultivating tea and compressing the leaves
into bowl-shaped mass, known as Tuo Cha in Chinese. They also love
bathing in  hotspring water. They uphold natural beauty.
</P>
<P>
Every year thousands of egrets make a huge fig tree in the city
as their habitat. But they have never been disturbed over the past
decade as everybody in the town knows that the bird is protected
by the state.
</P>
<P>
A fountain in the city is dominated by butterflies, hence its
name "Butterfly Fountain". On the 15th of April every year,
hundreds of butterflies are mysteriously dancing over the clear
water, sometimes linking up one another to form a long string
hanging from the tree above the fountain, undisturbed by the
presence of visitors.
</P>
<P>
As more and more tourists have ventured into Dali in recent
years, the people of the city have begun to put up posters,
reminding tourists of the importance of protecting the natural
environment.
</P>
<P>
Dali is also a world of flowers. A local valley called "
Wanhuaxi" is reputed as the "paradise of botanists". The city
holds a flower-worship festival every year.
</P>
<P>
Despite the fact that many modern buildings and boulevards have
been added to this ancient city since the founding of the People's
Republic of China, the old part of the city is still shrouded with
the air of an ancient utopian retreat.
</P>
<P>
Foreign tourists have thronged the city in recent years and
some even live there for a while. "I have been here for a week,"
said a tourist from Belgium."I love the environment and people
here."
</P>
<P>
A new cityscape tinged with the color of the 1990s has also
appeared in the old city. "Internet Bar" and signboards in English
can be seen along a street called by local people as "Foreign
Street".
</P>
<P>
The city has attracted a flock of artists, too. Nyima, a
Tibetan sculptor, said he is ready to buy a piece of land in Dali
and devote it to the environmental art. "It will mainly feature
simplicity and naturalness for which modern arts advocate," he
said.
</P>
<P>
"Dali people have always been living in good harmony with
nature," a local official, Zhang Jian remarked. "There is no need
to make deliberate preparations for the '99 horticulture
exposition." 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19990428.0277 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-04-28 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Issues Urban Water Resources Quality Report </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 28 (Xinhua) -- China has decided to issue water
resources quality report regularly for a number of its large and
medium-sized cities.
</P>
<P>
The Ministry of Water Resources on April 19 issued its first
ten-day water resources quality report of Beijing, Tianjin,
Chongqing, Wuhan, Nanchang, Kunming, Shenzhen, Dalian and eight
other cities.
</P>
<P>
An official with the ministry said the report, which is issued
at an interval of every 10 days, is aimed to encourage the
effective protection by municipal governments as well as people
from all walks of life of water sources for urbanites' drinking
water.
</P>
<P>
The report announces quality grades of water resources,
pollution index, and major pollutants in water resources of the
water supply areas.
</P>
<P>
The first water resources quality report indicated that Beijing,
Tianjin, Dalian, Taiyuan, Qingdao, Changsha, Nanjing, Kunming and
Urumqi have sound quality water resources. 
</P>
</TEXT>
