<DATE_TIME> 1999-04-28 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Continuous Rains Put Guangxi on Alert against Possible Flooding </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANNING, April 28 (Xinhua) -- Continuous rain in the past few
days has more than relieved a lingering drought in southwest
China's Guangxi Zhuang Autonomous Region and put local authorities
on alert against possible flooding.
</P>
<P>
Precipitation covered most parts of Guangxi between 21-26 this
month, with heavy rain and thunder storms hitting at least 58
counties in the region.
</P>
<P>
The rain has virtually eased the serious drought in Guangxi and
it now has refocused its attention on possible floods, a local
official said.
</P>
<P>
In the upper reaches of the Lijiang River, a major river in the
region, the rainfall reached 314 mm in the past few days, raising
the river's water level to 146.85 m, 1.85 m higher than official
warning line.
</P>
<P>
The sudden rise of the water level has forced water into some
parts of Guilin, one of the leading scenic cities in China.
</P>
<P>
Meteorologists have warned of possible abnormal weather in the
coming days and urged local residents to get prepared for flood
control.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
