In a further hint that the time for diplomacy was drawing near,
Dini said maybe it was time to send Italy's ambassador to
Yugoslavia Riccardo Sessa back to Belgrade.
</P>
<P>
Sessa was summoned to Rome for consultations on April 17 in a
move seen by some as a sign of Italy's impatience with Milosevic's
refusal to budge. 
