<HEADLINE> Bulgaria Suffers Huge Loss From Yugoslavia Crisis </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SOFIA, April 27 (Xinhua) -- Bulgaria has suffered 68 billion
leva (37 million U.S. dollars) direct losses since NATO launched
airstrikes against Yugoslavia on March 24.
</P>
<P>
Tourism and Trade Minister Valentin Vassilev said the actual
losses will be higher as they include the losses of all companies
and the reduced budget revenue, the jobs lost due to the decreased
capacities of some export-oriented enterprises, and assistance for
Kosovar refugees.
</P>
<P>
Average monthly losses related to embargo were 63 million
dollars and are expected to rise to 70 million dollars.
</P>
<P>
According to the Industry Ministry, the companies coming within
its jurisdiction have sustained 39.4 billion leva (21 million
dollars) losses.
</P>
<P>
Transport has suffered 24.32 billion leva (13 million dollars)
losses and four billion leva (two million dollars) in lost profits,
and the Committee of Post and Telecommunications has reported
losses of 40,000 dollars. 
</P>
