<HEADLINE> Shandong Province Improving Rural Electric Grids </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JINAN, April 28 (Xinhua) -- East China's Shandong Province is
expected to spend additional 7.99 billion yuan (96.3 million US
dollars) improving local rural electric grids this year, as part
of its effort to ensure local economic growth.
</P>
<P>
A sum of 4.55 billion yuan will be used to complete projects in
60 major counties and the remaining 3.44 billion yuan is to be
allocated for 70 percent of the projects in the 73 other local
counties.
</P>
<P>
The first package of local rural electric grids were
transformed last year at a cost of 1.5 billion yuan (180 million
US dollars). This helped cut the price for each kwh of electricity
by 0.12 yuan in those counties where electric grids were improved.
</P>
<P>
Three years ago, Shandong Province led the country in making
all rural families accessible to power supply. 
</P>
