<HEADLINE> Fujian Reports Success in Drug Control </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
FUZHOU, April 28 (Xinhua) -- East China's Fujian Province
reported success in cracking down on drug-related crimes last year,
according to the Provincial Public Security Department.
</P>
<P>
Last year police cracked a total of 1,577 drug-related cases,
170 more than in 1997, and confiscated 421.9 kg of drugs, up 18.7
percent, according to police statistics.
</P>
<P>
The seizure included 27.7 kg of heroine, 388.08 kg of "ice"
drug and 4.37 kg of other types of drugs, an official of the
department said, adding that 1,908 drug crime suspects were
arrested last year.
</P>
<P>
In an intensified effort in drug control, the coastal city of
Xiamen last year invested 20 million yuan in building drug
rehabilitation centers.
</P>
<P>
Currently, Fujian has five drug rehabilitation centers where a
total of 710 drug takers can be treated. 
</P>
