<HEADLINE> At Least 16 Civilians Killed in NATO Bombing Tuesday </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SURDULICA, Southern Yugoslavia, April 27 (Xinhua) -- At least
16 people, including 11 children aging between 5 and 15, were
killed Tuesday when NATO bombs hit the town of Surdulica, about
300 kilometers southeast of Belgrade.
</P>
<P>
The death toll was almost certain to rise as rescue workers
were digging the ruins in the hope of finding survivors.
</P>
<P>
The 16 victims were killed in two houses demolished by a NATO
bomb. Their remains were kept in a makeshift morgue. Some were
reduced to bits but none was whole.
</P>
<P>
Eleven people were wounded, two of them seriously.
</P>
<P>
This was the third time that the town came under NATO air raids.
A deserted military barrack nearby and two factories were targeted
in the previous two attacks.
</P>
<P>
Residents said between 12:05 and 12:25 local time, NATO fired
16 missiles on the town, destroying at least seven houses and
damaging more than 300. 
</P>
