<HEADLINE> U.S. House Committee Opposes Declaring War Against Belgrade </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, April 27 (Xinhua) -- A major House of
Representatives committee Tuesday voted against two separate
resolutions which demand the United States either formally declare
war against Yugoslavia or end its military involvement in the
Balkans.
</P>
<P>
The House International Relations Committee voted unanimously
against a motion that the U.S. formally declare war against
Yugoslavia.
</P>
<P>
The committee also voted 30-19 to recommend that the House
reject another motion for the U.S. to pull out of the conflict.
</P>
<P>
The United States is currently playing a leading role in the
brutal airstrikes by the North Atlantic Treaty Organization (NATO)
against Yugoslavia.
</P>
<P>
Both proposals will be put to a vote by the full House on
Wednesday though they were rejected by the committee.
</P>
<P>
