<HEADLINE> European Parliament President: EU Must Lead in Balkan Reconstruction </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SOFIA, April 27 (Xinhua) -- The European Union (EU) must play a
leading role in the reconstruction of the Balkan region after the
end of the Kosovo conflict, European Parliament President Jose
Maria Gil-Robles said here Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Addressing the opening session of the seventh meeting of the
parliamentary presidents of the countries bidding for EU
membership, Gil-Robles said the NATO strikes against Yugoslavia
had "seriously" destabilized the situation in the Balkans.
</P>
<P>
He said the EU was "very much aware of the implications of this
tragedy for all the countries of the region", calling it a
terrible moment in the history of Europe.
</P>
<P>
Bulgarian National Assembly Chairman Yordan Sokolov said the
crisis in Yugoslavia had a particularly adverse effect on Bulgaria
because of this country's geographical location, and it created
considerable difficulties for Bulgaria in its preparations for EU
membership.
</P>
<P>
He urged the EU to work out a clear policy to provide more
support to southeast Europe to alleviate the negative political
and economic impact of the Kosovo crisis.
</P>
<P>
The meeting is attended by the parliamentary leaders of all
countries taking part in the EU enlargement process, which are
Cyprus, the Czech Republic, Estonia, Hungary, Latvia, Lithuania,
Malta, Poland, Romania, Slovakia and Slovenia. 
</P>
</TEXT>
