<HEADLINE> NATO to Deploy Planes in Hungary to Strengthen Strikes on Yugoslavia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUDAPEST, April 27 (Xinhua) -- The Hungarian government Tuesday
accepted NATO's request to deploy 20 tanker planes in the country
in a bid to strengthen NATO bombing against Yugoslavia.
</P>
<P>
These planes and their auxiliaries will be deployed in the
Airport Number One of Budapest adjacent to the Number Two Airport
for civil and international civilian flights, said a government
spokesman. Eight of the tanker planes will arrive this evening and
the rest in the coming days.
</P>
<P>
On March 24 when NATO unleashed airstrikes on Yugoslavia, the
Hungary parliament decided to allow NATO to use Hungarian airspace,
airports, military service installations and commanding systems
during its military operation against Yugoslavia. 
</P>
