<DOCNO> XIE19990428.0313 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-04-28 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Giant Tumor Removed from Two-year old Chinese Girl </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIANJIN, April 28 (Xinhua) -- A two year old girl has had a
massive tumor successfully removed from her abdomen in north
China's Tianjin Municipality.
</P>
<P>
Doctors found a 3.5 kilogram tumor in the left part of Xue
Mengmeng's abdomen last September after her mother discovered a
fist-sized bulge.
</P>
<P>
It was diagnosed as a tumor immediately but doctors were
cautious about operating for fear of complications which often
occur during this operation.
</P>
<P>
Over the last six months the tumor was growing and became so
big before the operation that the girl could hardly walk and could
only take liquid food.
</P>
<P>
Doctor of the General Hospital attached to the Tianjin Medical
Sciences University, Shang Zhongliang, in charge of the operation,
said that as the girl became weaker so the operation became
riskier.
</P>
<P>
However, in an operation that lasted for over three hours the
tumor was removed and found to be just a little bigger than a
volleyball and almost a third of the girl's weight.
</P>
<P>
Doctors noted that though it is a common disease among children,
discovering such a big tumor is rare.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
