<HEADLINE> Hodgson Answers Inter Call </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, April 27 (Xinhua) -- Former Blackburn manager Roy
Hodgson is returning to his previous job at Inter Milan, according
to local reports on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The 51-year-old will coach Inter's first team until the end of
the season when former Juventus coach Marcello Lippi will take
over on a permanent basis.
</P>
<P>
He was in charge at the Italian club from 1995 to 1997 before
managing Blackburn until his dismissal from Ewood Park last
November.
</P>
<P>
"Internazionale announces that Mr. Roy Hodgson, from today
until the end of the season, will be the technical director of the
first team squad," said a statement from the club.
</P>
<P>
Hodgson will work alongside Luciano Castellini, who was
appointed caretaker coach on 23 March after the resignation of
Romanian Mircea Lucescu.
</P>
<P>
His task is to salvage what has been a disastrous season for
last year's UEFA Cup winners.
</P>
<P>
They are ninth in Serie A, 10 points behind leaders Lazio and
lost to Manchester United in the European Cup quarter-finals.
</P>
<P>
Star player Ronaldo is reportedly considering leaving the club
after his car was attacked by fans following last week's 3-1
defeat to Udinese. 
</P>
