<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Majoli Enters Second Round </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ZAGREB, April 27 (Xinhua) -- Local favorite Iva Majoli downed
Zuzana Heidova of the Czech Republic 6-2, 6-4 in the opening round
of the Bol Ladies Open on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Majoli, a former French Open champion, hit with authority and
accuracy, clearly reveling in the bright sunshine and red clay,
her best surface.
</P>
<P>
Still, the crowd was bemoaning the absence of Lucic, who
vaulted to prominence as a 15-year-old prodigy at this Adriatic
island resort two years ago, winning the title in her debut
tournament, then defending her crown in 1998.
</P>
<P>
In other matches, fifth-seeded Sarah Pitkowski of France
defeated Janette Husarova of Slovakia, 6-2, 6-2. Sandra Kleinova
of the Czech Republic beat Amanda Grahame of Austria, 6-3, 6-7 (7-
9), 7-5 and Spaniard Cristina Torrens-Valero routed Barbara
Schwartz, also of Austria, 6-2, 6-4.
</P>
<P>
A local youngster, Jelena Kostanic, came back to oust Slovene
Katarina Srepotnik, 6-4, 1-6, 6-2, while Argentine Mariana Diaz
Oliva edged another Slovenian, Tina Krizan, 2-6, 6-0, 7-6 (7-3).
</P>
<P>
Czech Adriana Gersi rallied back from a set down to win against
Tina Pisnik, another Slovene, 0-6, 6-4, 7-5 and Raluca Sandu of
Romania beat Amelie Cocheteux of France, 6-4, 7-5.
</P>
<P>
Croat Silvija Talaja squeezed past Catarina Cristea of Romania,
7-6 (7-2), 7-6 (7-3), while Conchita Martinez of Spain defeated
Briton Lucie Ahl, 7-5, 6-0. 
</P>
</TEXT>
