<HEADLINE> Kafelnikov Falls in First Round </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PRAGUE, April 27 (Xinhua) -- Yevgeny Kafelnikov, who will
become world number one next week, dropped to Richard Fromberg in
three sets in the first round of the Czech Open on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Fromberg beat the Australian Open champion and the top-seeded
Russian 6-4, 2-6, 6-4. But Kafelnikov will still take the No. 1
spot from Pete Sampras, who is resting this week because of injury.
</P>
<P>
In other first-round matches, third-seeded Cedric Pioline of
France beat Czech Republic's Jiri Novak 7-6 (8-6), 0-6, 7-6 (7-4),
seed No. 7 Nicolas Lapenti of Ecuador defeated Czech Radovan
Svetlik 6-0, 6-4, eighth-seeded Andrew Ilie of Australia defeated
Sebastian Prieto of Argentina 6-2, 6-4 and fourth-seeded Marat
Safin of Russia lost to Czech qualifier Tomas Zib 1-6, 6-1, 7-5.
</P>
<P>
The seed No. 2, Goran Ivanisevic of Croatia, led Germany's
Markus Hantschk 7-6 (7-4) when the match was suspended because of
darkness.
</P>
<P>
Czech player Bohdan Ulihrach, seeded No. 6, withdrew from the
tournament because of a high fever. 
</P>
