<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Kidney Transplant Successful in Heilongjiang </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARBIN, April 28 (Xinhua) -- Physicians in China's northernmost
Heilongjiang Province have successfully transplanted a kidney
donated by his mother into the body of a 24-year-old man.
</P>
<P>
The operation was a rare homoplastic transplant using an organ
provided by a family member, said one of the doctors at the No.2
Hospital of the Harbin Medical Sciences University.
</P>
<P>
The patient, named Liu Hui, had been suffering from kidney
disorder for a long time and was kept alive by frequent blood
transfusions.
</P>
<P>
His mother donate her left kidney, but she suffers from a vein
and artery deformity, which caused great difficulty in the
procedure.
</P>
<P>
At present, the blood pressure and pulse of both the mother and
son are normal, and the doctors are carefully monitoring the
patient to see if his body rejects the transplanted kidney.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
