<DATE_TIME> 1999-04-28 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Shanxi Implements UNFPA-Funded Health Program </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TAIYUAN, April 28 (Xinhua) -- Linxian, the largest poor county
in north Shanxi province, has launched a health and family
planning program funded by the United Nations Population Fund (
UNFPA).
</P>
<P>
The program, part of the cooperation between the Chinese
government and the UNFPA, is designed to promote reproductive
health and is also aimed at controlling the growth of the
population.
</P>
<P>
With the implementation of the two-and-half year program, 60
percent of women in Linxian county will be taught at least three
contraceptive methods and the abortion rate is expected to drop to
0.3 percent from 0.5 percent.
</P>
<P>
The program is costing 420,000 U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
An additional 32 counties in 22 provinces, municipalities and
autonomous regions in China are also covered by the same UNFPA
program.
</P>
<P>
The concept of reproductive health was introduced during the
International Conference on Population and Development in Cairo in
1994. The conference promoted reproductive rights and worldwide
improvements of related health care matters. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
