<HEADLINE> Overseas Investors Invited to Assess Local Government </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JINAN, April 28 (Xinhua) -- Overseas investors in Jinan,
capital of east China's Shandong Province, have been asked to join
in the assessment of local government departments.
</P>
<P>
Directors of overseas funded enterprises will be asked to
answer a questionnaire drawn up by the local government to seek
their views and suggestions about government work.
</P>
<P>
The departments to be assessed include the bureaus of industry
and commerce, taxation, public security, traffic control, and
telecommunications.
</P>
<P>
Vice-Mayor Gang Zhanbiao said this move is a major step by the
city government to improve the work of its departments and to
create a better business environment.
</P>
<P>
Jinan has to date approved 2,350 overseas funded enterprises,
with total investments of 4.31 billion U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
Although most of these enterprises have been operating smoothly,
Gang said there are complaints about various problems such as
illicit fees, and a dilatory attitude to work by some government
officials. 
</P>
</TEXT>
