<HEADLINE> Special Steel Tubes To Rebuild Qijiang Bridge </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, April 28 (Xinhua) -- The collapsed Qijiang Rainbow
Bridge in southwest China's Chongqing municipality will be rebuilt
with 496 tons of high quality, seamless steel tubes produced by
the Shanghai Baoshan Iron and Steel Company.
</P>
<P>
According to a senior official from the company, this show of
faith indicates that the work units responsible for the design and
reconstruction of the bridge have learned a lesson and paid great
attention to the quality of construction materials.
</P>
<P>
The bridge collapsed on January 4, killing 40 people and
injuring 14 others and the accident has shocked the nation.
</P>
<P>
One official held responsible has been sentenced to death and
12 others, including an engineer, a materials supplier, and
several government officials have received prison terms ranging
from three to 13 years.
</P>
<P>
Steel tubes produced by the company in accordance with the
requirements of the ISO 9000 standards have been widely used in
the construction of key State projects in China, including the
Pudong International Airport in Shanghai, the Nanjing
International Airport and the Jiangyin Yangtze River Bridge in
Jiangsu Province. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
