<HEADLINE> Ronaldo Hints to Leave Inter </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, April 27 (Xinhua) -- Ronaldo said Tuesday angry fans
actions upon him were intolerable and hinted to leave Inter Milan
if violence repeated.
</P>
<P>
The Brazilian striker's car was hit by a bottle thrown by a fan,
who was apparently furious about last Sunday's 3-1 home defeat by
Udinese, as it was leaving the San Siro Stadium.
</P>
<P>
Ronaldo's parents, sister and nephew were all in the car but no-
one was hurt.
</P>
<P>
"In this climate of tension and fear, somebody could decide to
leave Inter," Ronaldo said.
</P>
<P>
Ronaldo, who was in Spain for a friendly between Brazil and his
former club Barcelona, said he had not yet thought of leaving
Inter.
</P>
<P>
Inter issued a statement on Monday evening, deploring the fans
who threw stones and bottles at players' cars. 
</P>
