<DATE_TIME> 1999-04-28 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> U.S. "For-Profit" Education Industry A Multi-billion </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Los Angeles, April 27 (Xinhua) -- The "for-profit" education
and training industry in the United States is now 70 billion U.S.
dollars, growing at 13 percent a year, according to a report
released Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
In addition, since 1994, education and training companies have
raised more than 3.4 billion U.S. dollars of equity capital
through more than 38 initial public offerings and 30 follow-on
offerings, said Merrill Lynch, one of the world's leading
financial institutions.
</P>
<P>
Overall, in the United States, the education and training
industry, both for-profit and not-for-profit, reached 740 billion
U.S. dollars in 1998 and is growing at 6 percent a year. Globally,
the industry already tops 2 trillion U.S. dollars annually.
</P>
<P>
The transformation to a knowledge-based economy is creating a
fertile environment in the for-profit education and training
industry and a significant opportunity for investors in the
foreseeable future, the report said.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, the report said, the educational needs of the
knowledge economy, contrasted with the current system's inability
to fill those needs, provide innovative companies with open-ended
opportunities for growth.
</P>
<P>
On new things that are rapidly evolving in education and
training, Merrill Lynch said that technology-based delivery of
education -- distributed learning -- is providing greater access
to more at a lower cost. Educational portals creating an
education-focused gateway to the Internet available to all from
kindergarten to adults is especially a big opportunity for the
for-profit education and training industry.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
