<HEADLINE> Two Injured in Strong Bomb Explosion in Athens </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATHENS, April 27 (Xinhua) -- A bomb exploded Tuesday night at
the entrance of Greece's Athens Intercontinental hotel, injuring
two people, including one seriously.
</P>
<P>
The strong explosion occurred at 23:37 local time, the
semi-official Athens News Agency (ANA) reported.
</P>
<P>
No further details were immediately available.
</P>
<P>
On April 15, a home-made bomb exploded outside a showcase of
the Detroit-based General Motors in Maroussi, northern suburb of
Athens, damaging three parked cars. 
