<HEADLINE> Wall Street Stocks End Mixed </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, April 27 (Xinhua) -- Wall Street stocks ended mixed
Tuesday with the Dow Jones industrial average rising into record
territory and the technology heavy Nasdaq index falling.
</P>
<P>
The Dow closed up 113.12 at the record high of 10,831.71 as
AT&AMP;T and DuPont, both Dow components, reported strong earnings in
the first quarter of this year. AT&AMP;T gained 61 cents a share,
beating the expectation of 57 cents while DuPont got 66 cents a
share, beating analysts' expected 60 cents.
</P>
<P>
The Nasdaq index was down 49.64 at 2,602.41 on profit-taking.
The index rose 61.36 at 2,652.05 Monday.
</P>
<P>
The Standard &AMP; Poor's 500 index rose 2.76 at 1,362.80 while the
NYSE index rose 4.44 at 643.27.
</P>
<P>
The American Stock Exchange composite index rose 2.47 at 774.07
and the Russell 2000 index of smaller companies rose 0.19 to
435.16.
</P>
<P>
Advancing issues outnumbered decliners by a 9-to-7 margin on
the New York Stock Exchange, with 1,681 up, 1,308 down and 572
unchanged.
</P>
<P>
NYSE volume increased to 888.21 million shares from 706.62
million in the previous session. 
</P>
</TEXT>
