<DOCNO> XIE19990428.0349 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-04-28 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> U.S. Says Willing to Help East Timor Referendum </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, April 27 (Xinhua) -- The United States is willing
to take part in organizing a referendum on autonomy in East
Timor in August, a State Department official said on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The official's remarks came as Indonesian President B.J.
Habibie announced after talks with Australian Prime Minister John
Howard earlier on Tuesday that he had accepted all of a U.N.
draft on the referendum arrangements "without any changes."
</P>
<P>
"This is an important step towards clearing the way for the
U.N. consultation process with the Eat Timorese on August 8,"
the official said.
</P>
<P>
"The United States wishes to play an active and positive role
in support of the U.N. process. We are discussing the specific
ways in which the U.S. will assist but no final decisions have
been made," he added.
</P>
<P>
Indonesia invaded East Timor in 1975, one year after the
Portuguese pulled out. 
</P>
</TEXT>
